Description:
Taste the real Ho Chi Minh City by this Phu My shore excursion. Visit the sacred Heavenly Lady Pagoda, sample the traditional food, stroll along Ben Thanh Market, enjoy special Vietnamese coffee at oldest coffee shop in the alley, and make your camera ready by driving through various photo spots around the city.
⭐Pick-up & Drop off From Nha Rong, Hiep Phuoc, Phu Huu, Phu My Port;
⭐Visit All HCMC’s Best Bits, Including Notre-Dame Cathedral & General Post Office, Thien Hau Pagoda, War Remnants Museum, Ben Thanh Market, photo stops around the city;
⭐Enjoy lunch with Vietnamese traditional food as Vietnamese pancake & rice noodles with grilled pork/fried roll – specialty food of the city;
⭐Visit an over 80-year-old cafe hidden in an alley & interact with the nice host & learn how to brew the unique Vot coffee.
*****This private tour's approximately 8 hours or longer depending on your time constraints.
We always make sure that you return on-time to board the cruise ship.

Explore the old and the new of Ho Chi Minh City through this 2-days Ho Chi Minh Shore Excursions from cruise port for insights into its tumultuous past. Experience the city’s dynamics and vitality in the present days as you pass by dizzying traffic and sleek skyscrapers.
⭐ HIGHLIGHTS
- Pick-up & Drop off From Nha Rong, Hiep Phuoc, Phu Huu, Phu My Port
- Visit All HCMC’s Best Bits, Including Notre-Dame Cathedral & General Post Office, Thien Hau Pagoda, War Remnants Museum, Reunification Palace, photo stops around the city;
- Enjoy street food by motorbike or walking, view beautiful Ho Chi Minh by night;
- Learn how the Viet Cong fighters navigated a network of war tunnels;
- Visit The Fascinating Underground Bunkers (And Crawl In!);
- Enjoy lunch at local restaurant with special Vietnamese traditional food;
⭐Duration: 2 Days. We always make sure that you return on-time to board the cruise ship.

Forget about the faraway Ho Chi Minh City when you have so much to discover in the nearby Vung Tau, a seaside city famous for the only petroleum base of Viet Nam. In this Vung Tau shore excursion, you can admire a huge Jesus statue, the 12-meter long marble statue of Lying Buddha and the signature Vung Tau Lighthouse.
⭐ HIGHLIGHTS:
- Visit the spectacular Statue of Jesus;
- Admire the sheer magnitude of the majestic statue of Lying Buddha at Nirvana Pagoda;
- Witness the Grandeur of White Palace;
- Enjoy lunch with Vietnamese traditional food as Vietnamese pancake & rice noodles with grilled pork/fried roll – specialty food of the city;
- Visit Whale Temple & Vung Tau Lighthouse.
⭐ Duration: 8 hours or longer depending on your time constraints. At the end of the private tour, we always make sure that you return on-time to board the cruise ship.
⭐ Meeting point: Port gate outside (Vung Tau Port or Phu My port).
